The paper deals with Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) for face synthesis, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a new loss function to address the problem of mismatching distributions in self-domain synthesis, which is a machine learning problem (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of landmarks to guide the face synthesis, which is a common technique in computer vision and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper involves the generation of images, which is a topic in computer graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM). Overall, the paper is likely to belong to cs.CV, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, and cs.MM.
